.TH XPL-F 1 "2026-03-26" "xpl-f" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xpl-f \- terminal file explorer with vim-style keybindings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xpl-f
.RI [ directory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B xpl-f
is a TUI file explorer built with Zig and libvaxis.
It provides vim-style navigation, dual panels, fuzzy search,
file preview, bookmarks, and clipboard operations.
.PP
If
.I directory
is given, xpl-f opens in that directory.
Otherwise it opens in the current working directory.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS General
.TP
.B F1
Help popup
.TP
.B q
Quit
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B j / Down
Move down
.TP
.B k / Up
Move up
.TP
.B l / Enter
Open file or enter directory
.TP
.B h / \-
Go to parent directory
.TP
.B 0 / Home
Go to top
.TP
.B $ / End
Go to bottom
.TP
.B Ctrl+s
Toggle dual panel
.TP
.B Tab
Switch focus between panels
.SS Search & Filter
.TP
.B /
Fuzzy search
.TP
.B r
Search & replace in filenames
.TP
.B ?
Find recursive
.TP
.B \e\e
Tree view
.SS Operations
.TP
.B Space
Select entry
.TP
.B Ctrl+a
Select all (toggle)
.TP
.B Ctrl+d
Drag & drop (via ripdrag)
.TP
.B n
New file or directory
.TP
.B Y
Duplicate file
.TP
.B D
Delete file or selection
.TP
.B x
Cut to clipboard
.TP
.B y
Copy to clipboard
.TP
.B p
Paste from clipboard
.TP
.B c
Copy path to system clipboard
.TP
.B F2
Rename (edit mode)
.TP
.B F3
Preview file contents
.TP
.B F4
Open shell in current directory
.TP
.B F5
Refresh directory listing
.TP
.B m
Toggle bookmark on current directory
.TP
.B b
Open bookmarks list
.TP
.B .
Toggle hidden files
.SH PREVIEW
Pressing
.B F3
opens a floating preview window.
.PP
Text files are shown with line numbers; scroll with
.B j/k\fR.
Directories show a recursive tree view (up to 3 levels).
Binary files display
.IR "[binary file]" .
.SH FILE OPENING
Binary file types (pdf, png, mp4, etc.) are opened with
.BR xdg-open (1)
in the background.
.PP
Text files are opened in
.B $EDITOR
(fallback:
.BR vi ).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Text editor for opening files. Defaults to
.BR vi .
.SH AUTHORS
Written as a Zig learning project with assistance from Claude Code.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ranger (1),
.BR lf (1),
.BR nnn (1)
